"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"Since making its initial $250-million Bitcoin investment in August 2020, MicroStrategy has gone on to purchase billions of dollars in Bitcoin in separate buys using the companyâ€™s cash on hand in addition to [sales of convertible senior notes](https://cointelegraph.com/news/microstrategy-raising-600m-no-900m-to-buy-more-bitcoin) in private offerings to institutional buyers. Though there are cases in which the [business intelligence firm bought the dip](https://cointelegraph.com/news/microstrategy-buys-the-dip-acquires-10m-in-bitcoin), some buys followed the price surges in early 2021 when the BTC price was more than $50,000.\\n\\n***Related: [MicroStrategy pledges to buy more BTC despite paper loss on its holdings of $424.8M in Q2](https://cointelegraph.com/news/microstrategy-pledges-to-buy-more-btc-despite-paper-loss-on-its-holdings-of-424-8m-in-q2)***\\n\\nAccording to data from [Cointelegraph Markets Pro](https://pro.cointelegraph.com/?via=news), the price of Bitcoin is $48,684 at the time of publication, having fallen more than 25% in the last 30 days. The crypto asset has been hovering near $50,000 since [dipping to the $42,000s](https://cointelegraph.com/news/bitcoin-rebounds-on-wall-street-open-as-exchange-btc-reserves-plunge-after-42k-dip) on Friday.\",\"timestamp\":1639141661,\"title\":\"principle and the three joint communiques between China\"},\"digest\":\"yYsYhSyHPH1n3Bj8Wbdoq7Rdhwb7FOlEo9uTSIBD1fA\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0x4B5acb76784de367343c0836a5C3530f036438dD\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"91D7l3wwuo1QNEdzWBNkLcnIuM7G2-7UOsD0GlZhvW4\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"j82gw65shi2oZ7Kebu9wDdhw44xgwr7F4gB2Ilb5COw\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"Vk38huKpnyDISiwrxEigfeSgXWRnBVkXH0nLj-_CdePvm8sRVxbE6EAcFAsE5YVromobQABOJ5QWuou7nHbwNA\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0x38018d4b9725dce9215c7cdeb74ebd58244c5c9b153ad6e1a86fde27e1a92459118c097f11e4fa2d1